   buf[255] = '\0';
   ```
   
   GLOBAL FIX: Replace all unsafe string functions with bounded alternatives,
   and consider adopting a safer string API design (e.g., using bounded string
   types, compile-time bounds, or custom wrappers) throughout the codebase to
   prevent such overflows at design time.
